message: This is not the first time that this page has been a target of harassment and trolls, with past false claims written on him and his wife (check the history), and entire sections being altered and/or deleted. This is just another attack on the page and this artist.
/* Your submission at Articles for creation: The Band Famous (February 21) */
Thank you for your help!
Thank you, RadioFan!
/* Question Regarding Former Article That Was Up */
Question, Seeking Insight & Guidance for Undeletion
Start of Live Canvas
Linking related article.
Warm Wishes!
Introduction
A request for aid on an article you published.
Keep improving this article, but keep it up.
I'm on the border of finding it notable and of not finding it notable. I am requesting additional references. It may meet criteria to stay up, but not for certain I am convinced of this yet.
No cited verifiable and reliable sources, in fact there are no in-line citations for references whatsoever.
Too much writing and not enough notability to back it up. Reduce the size of this article to fit the length of references, or else I agree it does not meet the criteria to remain on Wikipedia.

No verifiable or reliable sources referenced? Three years is a long time to cite references, I'm quite puzzled why none are here if it's true they were on TV and signed to the record label in the article.
Adding my thoughts to discussion after checking the references in this article.

Repeatedly removing reliable sources constitutes as disruptive editing and thereby constitutes as Wikihounding.
